#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.232"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.232:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.232:0.2"
msgid "18. Samuddavagga"
msgstr "18. The Ocean"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 232. Koṭṭhikasutta → koṭṭhitasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.232:0.3"
msgid "232. Koṭṭhikasutta"
msgstr "232. With Koṭṭhita"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: mahākoṭṭhiko → mahākoṭṭhito (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.232:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko bārāṇasiyaṃ "
"viharanti isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Sāriputta and Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita were staying near "
"Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana."

msgctxt "sn35.232:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhita came out of retreat, went "
"to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn35.232:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Sāriputta:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.163"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, cakkhu rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, rūpā cakkhussa "
"saṃyojanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, which is it? Is the eye the fetter of sights, or are "
"sights the fetter of the eye?"

msgctxt "sn35.232:2.2"
msgid "jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, rasā jivhāya saṃyojanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Is the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:2.3"
msgid "mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, dhammā manassa saṃyojanan”ti?"
msgstr "mind the fetter of thoughts, or are thoughts the fetter of the mind?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso koṭṭhika, cakkhu rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rūpā cakkhussa "
"saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Koṭṭhita, the eye is not the fetter of sights, nor are sights the "
"fetter of the eye."

msgctxt "sn35.232:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them."

msgctxt "sn35.232:3.3"
msgid "na jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rasā jivhāya saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:3.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:3.5"
msgid "na mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na dhammā manassa saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"mind is not the fetter of thoughts, nor are thoughts the fetter of the mind."

msgctxt "sn35.232:3.6"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: balībaddo → balivaddo (bj, pts1) | balibaddo (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.232:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kāḷo ca balībaddo odāto ca balībaddo ekena dāmena vā "
"yottena vā saṃyuttā assu."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a black ox and a white ox yoked by a single harness or "
"yoke."

msgctxt "sn35.232:4.2"
msgid "Yo nu kho evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Would it be right to say that"

msgctxt "sn35.232:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘kāḷo balībaddo odātassa balībaddassa saṃyojanaṃ, odāto balībaddo kāḷassa "
"balībaddassa saṃyojanan’ti, sammā nu kho so vadamāno vadeyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"the black ox is the yoke of the white ox, or the white ox is the yoke of the "
"black ox?”"

# The lack of close -ti makes it impossible to determine exactly where this quote ends and the next begins. BB treats the following sentences as belonging to Kotthita, but both MS and PTS punctuate as if it’s Sariputta. However, in SN 41.1 the use of vocatives in an otherwise identical passage shows that BB is correct.
msgctxt "sn35.232:4.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend."

msgctxt "sn35.232:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso, kāḷo balībaddo odātassa balībaddassa saṃyojanaṃ, na odāto "
"balībaddo kāḷassa balībaddassa saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The black ox is not the yoke of the white ox, nor is the white ox the yoke "
"of the black ox."

msgctxt "sn35.232:4.6"
msgid ""
"Yena ca kho te ekena dāmena vā yottena vā saṃyuttā taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr "The yoke there is the single harness or yoke that they’re yoked by.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:5.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, na cakkhu rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rūpā cakkhussa "
"saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, the eye is not the fetter of sights, nor are sights the "
"fetter of the eye."

msgctxt "sn35.232:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them."

msgctxt "sn35.232:5.3"
msgid "na jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:5.4"
msgid "na mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na dhammā manassa saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"mind is not the fetter of thoughts, nor are thoughts the fetter of the mind."

msgctxt "sn35.232:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.164"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: paññāyetha → paññāyati (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.232:6.1"
msgid ""
"Cakkhu vā, āvuso, rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ abhavissa, rūpā vā cakkhussa "
"saṃyojanaṃ, nayidaṃ brahmacariyavāso paññāyetha sammā dukkhakkhayāya."
msgstr ""
"If the eye were the fetter of sights, or if sights were the fetter of the "
"eye, this living of the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering "
"would not be found."

msgctxt "sn35.232:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, āvuso, na cakkhu rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rūpā cakkhussa "
"saṃyojanaṃ;"
msgstr "However, since this is not the case, but"

msgctxt "sn35.232:6.3"
msgid ""
"yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ, "
"tasmā brahmacariyavāso paññāyati sammā dukkhakkhayāya … pe …."
msgstr ""
"the fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them, "
"this living of the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering is "
"found."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:7.1"
msgid ""
"Jivhā, āvuso, rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ abhavissa, rasā vā jivhāya saṃyojanaṃ, "
"nayidaṃ brahmacariyavāso paññāyetha sammā dukkhakkhayāya."
msgstr "If the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:7.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, āvuso, na jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rasā jivhāya saṃyojanaṃ;"
" yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha "
"saṃyojanaṃ, tasmā brahmacariyavāso paññāyati sammā dukkhakkhayāya … pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:8.1"
msgid ""
"Mano vā, āvuso, dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ abhavissa, dhammā vā manassa "
"saṃyojanaṃ, nayidaṃ brahmacariyavāso paññāyetha sammā dukkhakkhayāya."
msgstr ""
"mind were the fetter of thoughts, or if thoughts were the fetter of the "
"mind, this living of the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering "
"would not be found."

msgctxt "sn35.232:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, āvuso, na mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na dhammā manassa "
"saṃyojanaṃ;"
msgstr "However, since this is not the case, but"

msgctxt "sn35.232:8.3"
msgid ""
"yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ, "
"tasmā brahmacariyavāso paññāyati sammā dukkhakkhayāya."
msgstr ""
"the fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them, "
"this living of the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering is "
"found."

# It’s unclear to me whether this phrase is looking back to the previous case or forward to the next. It is most commonly used at the end of a section, but sometimes also at the beginning.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:9.1"
msgid ""
"Imināpetaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā na cakkhu rūpānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, "
"na rūpā cakkhussa saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr "This too is a way to understand how this is so."

msgctxt "sn35.232:9.2"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ …"
" pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:9.3"
msgid "na jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:9.4"
msgid "na mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na dhammā manassa saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:9.5"
msgid ""
"Yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.165"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:10.1"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho, āvuso, bhagavato cakkhu."
msgstr "The Buddha has an eye"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.2"
msgid "Passati bhagavā cakkhunā rūpaṃ."
msgstr "with which he sees a sight."

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.3"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr "But he has no desire and greed,"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.4"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr "for his mind is well freed."

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.5"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho, āvuso, bhagavato sotaṃ."
msgstr "The Buddha has an ear …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.6"
msgid "Suṇāti bhagavā sotena saddaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.7"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.8"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.9"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho, āvuso, bhagavato ghānaṃ."
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.10"
msgid "Ghāyati bhagavā ghānena gandhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.11"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.12"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.13"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho, āvuso, bhagavato jivhā."
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.14"
msgid "Sāyati bhagavā jivhāya rasaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.15"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.16"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.17"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho, āvuso, bhagavato kāyo."
msgstr "The Buddha has a body"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.18"
msgid "Phusati bhagavā kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "with which he senses touch."

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.19"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr "But he has no desire and greed,"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.20"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr "for his mind is well freed. "

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.21"
msgid "Vijānāti bhagavā manasā dhammaṃ."
msgstr "The Buddha knows thought with his mind."

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.22"
msgid "Chandarāgo bhagavato natthi."
msgstr "But he has no desire and greed,"

msgctxt "sn35.232:10.23"
msgid "Suvimuttacitto bhagavā."
msgstr "for his mind is well freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.232:11.1"
msgid ""
"Iminā kho etaṃ, āvuso, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā na cakkhu rūpānaṃ "
"saṃyojanaṃ, na rūpā cakkhussa saṃyojanaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"This too is a way to understand how the eye is not the fetter of sights, nor "
"are sights the fetter of the eye."

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.2"
msgid ""
"yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them."

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.3"
msgid "Na sotaṃ …"
msgstr "The ear …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.4"
msgid "na ghānaṃ …"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.5"
msgid "na jivhā rasānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na rasā jivhāya saṃyojanaṃ;"
msgstr "tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.6"
msgid ""
"yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.7"
msgid "Na kāyo …"
msgstr "body …"

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.8"
msgid "na mano dhammānaṃ saṃyojanaṃ, na dhammā manassa saṃyojanaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"mind is not the fetter of thoughts, nor are thoughts the fetter of the mind."

msgctxt "sn35.232:11.9"
msgid ""
"yañca tattha tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandarāgo, taṃ tattha "
"saṃyojanan”ti."
msgstr ""
"The fetter there is the desire and greed that arises from the pair of them.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.232:11.10"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
